description:
### Have you ever thought to extract a person 3D model from a mono(2D) picture?

#### Is possible to get information like:
 - The distance between people;
 - How many people are in the same picture?;
 - To where are they looking?;
 - Who's in the front and who's behind?;
 - These people are fat or thin?
 - Are they sitting or standing?
 - And more!

In this talk, we will learn more about DensePose, a Facebook project to map all human pixels of an RGB image, to a 3D surface of the human body in real-time \0/
